HEADWORD: Nabk
<hw>Nabk</hw> <pr>(n⟦acr⟧bk)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar.
<ets>nabiqa</ets>, <ets>nibqa</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The
edible berries of the <spn>Zizyphys Lotus</spn>, a tree of Northern
Africa, and Southwestern Europe.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>nubk</asp>.]</altsp> See <er>Lotus</er> <sd>(b)</sd>, and
<er>Sadr</er>.⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

